<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" COLOR="#333399"><b>Palarran</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399"><B>Nature lover</B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Joined: Jun 15, 2001</FONT><br><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posts: 32</FONT></td><TD valign="top"><img src="/boards/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posted: 2001-08-02 23:39&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">A bard. <IMG SRC="/boards/images/smiles/icon_wink.gif"><BR>(Okay, so their lock picking and trap disarming skills are a BIT limited...)<BR><BR>I went with both a monk and bard once I started needing breaks as a druid.  Monk is now 45 and bard is 40 (mostly because I've been levelling up with RL friends who needed a monk more than a bard most of the time).  Both are a lot of fun to play depending on my mood.<BR><BR>I'd say go with a monk first.  Once you've mastered the ability to feign, both in terms of skill level and usage, you can explore areas relatively safely that you never could before.  (Monk's feign is generally better than a SK's feign since it's instant and breaks stuns.  Mend is also very nice for healing when I feign near death and there are no healers around...within 24 minutes I'm guaranteed to be back at full health.  A shadowknight can't heal himself nearly as fast in a dangerous place where he needs to stay feigned until he gets some health back, unless there are right clicky items that will help...)<BR><BR>You'll learn your way around even better when you start pulling as many groups will expect you to.  Shadowknights may be better for pulling the majority of the time, but monks are a close second when SK's aren't around, and there are still occasions when a monk would be a better puller than a SK.  It's also nice not to be so reliant on your equipment...I could probably hold my own in a group right now without wearing a thing, as long as the group has a proper tank.  I've seen it argued that the monk is the one class that could reach level 60 on 100pp worth of equipment (a set of cured silk armor).  On top of that, you get to spam mobs to death.  No one beats a monk for spamminess. <IMG SRC="/boards/images/smiles/icon_smile.gif"><BR><BR>After that, try something completely different...maybe a bard or enchanter.  It's good to see many aspects of the game, helps keep things interesting and gives you an appreciation of everything that is going on in a group.<BR><BR><font size=-1>[ This Message was edited by: Palarran on 2001-08-02 23:45 ]</font></FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#f7f5e6"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=325"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of Palarran"></a>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://www.bunniesofchaos.org" TARGET="_blank"><IMG SRC="/boards/images/www_icon.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Goto the website of Palarran"></a>
